comments.body:
@djnotes If you don't have much content could you reset your storage and see if this clears this up.

podman system reset

Note this will delete everything in your containers/storage.

@rhatdan  

>We see this when people login as root and su user. But if you login normaly via ssh or graphical login, systemd should setup the user session correctly. 

Actually I login via a normal user. Nevertheless, after following your `podman system reset` recommendation and restarting the computer, the issue was solved completely.
